influence the outcome of a roll, the points cancel each other out; no additional dice are rolled.\nYou regain your expended luck points when you finish a long rest.","maxCharges":3,"charges":3},{"name":"Bardic Inspiration (d6)","description":"As a bonus action, choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6.\nOnce within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the DM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.","maxCharges":3,"charges":3},{"name":"Cutting Words","description":"You learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling a Bardic Inspiration die and subtracting the number rolled from the creature's roll. You can choose to use this feature after the creature makes its roll, but before the DM determines whether the attack roll or ability check succeeds or fails, or before the creature deals its damage. The creature is immune if it can't hear you or if it's immune to being charmed.","resourceName":"Bardic Inspiration (d6)","resourceCost":1,"charges":3}],"proficiencies":["Language: Common","Disguise Kit","Language: Deep Speech","Lute","Light Armor","Simple Weapons","Rapiers","Longswords","Shortswords","Hand Crossbows","Drum","Lyre","Viol"],"inventory":[{"name":"Costume","count":3},{"name":"Favor of an admirer","count":1},{"name":"Belt Pouch","count":1},{"name":"Lute","description":"If you have pr